The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques in security applications, specifically in malware and intrusion detection. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also focuses on improving the robustness of ML classifiers against evasion attacks, which falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of feature space models and conserved features, which are common topics in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also mentions structure-based PDF malware detection and content-based detectors, which are relevant to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the approach in the context of realizable attacks, which may fall under the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
